#Find the significant feature with Principal Component Analysis(PCA)

def n_component_analysis(n, X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test, count):
    start = time.time()
    pca = PCA(n_components=n)
    print("Test #",count)
    print("PCA begin with n_components: {}".format(n));
    pca.fit(X_train)
    # 
    X_train_pca = pca.transform(X_train)
    X_test_pca = pca.transform(X_test)
    
    print('Model Training Begin')
    clf1 = svm.SVC()
    clf1.fit(X_train_pca, y_train)
    #  
    accuracy = clf1.score(X_test_pca, y_test)
    end = time.time()
    print('Model Training finished')
    print("Accuracy: {}\nTime Used: {} seconds".format(accuracy, int(end-start)))
    print("====================================================================\n")
    return accuracy

#random generate variance from 0.7-0.95
n_s = np.linspace(0.70, 0.90, num=20)

#finding the significant of features that correlate with the result 
accuracy = []
start_test = time.time()
count = 0
for idx,n in enumerate(n_s):
    tmp = n_component_analysis(n, x_train, y_train, x_test, y_test, idx)
    accuracy.append(tmp)

    
end_test=time.time()
used_time = end_test - start_test
print("Total Time Used: {} minutes {} seconds".format(int(used_time/60), int(used_time%60)))
print("====================================================================\n")
